import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the dataset
df = pd.read_csv('dataset.csv')

# Get the unique device models and user behavior classes
device_models = df['Device Model'].unique()
behavior_classes = df['User Behavior Class'].unique()

# Initialize a dictionary to store the count of each user behavior class for each device model
behavior_class_counts = {model: {class_: 0 for class_ in behavior_classes} for model in device_models}

# Count the number of users for each user behavior class and device model
for index, row in df.iterrows():
    behavior_class_counts[row['Device Model']][row['User Behavior Class']] += 1

# Create a figure and axis object
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

# Create a bar chart for each device model
for i, model in enumerate(device_models):
    ax.bar(i - 0.2, [behavior_class_counts[model][class_] for class_ in behavior_classes], width=0.2, label=model)

# Set the x-axis ticks and labels
ax.set_xticks(range(len(behavior_classes)))
ax.set_xticklabels(behavior_classes)

# Set the title and labels
ax.set_title('User Behavior Class Breakdown by Device Model')
ax.set_xlabel('User Behavior Class')
ax.set_ylabel('Count')

# Legend
ax.legend(title='Device Model', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')

# Show the plot
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
